Thank you for getting on the call this week! For your reference, here is the link to Events API for Server-Side Google Tag Manager (GTM)

Regarding questions for provisioning your own server for Event API vs using Google Cloud Platform (GCP), a couple of considerations:

  • When implementing through GTM, GCP can be a slightly more expensive server option.
    • But it provides the trade-off of convenience (embedded in GTM)
    • Built-in server creation with just a few clicks as part of Event API setup
  • Non-GCP options require a sufficient dev ops infrastructure. But if you have that infrastructure, you may prefer to keep data in-house.
    • You do not need a new server, the container will run alongside other services hosted by the domain.

Regarding non-GTM options, TikTok supports Event API integration with partner data platforms here.

Advantages:

  • Can be used alongside your GTM Pixel implementation
  • Server is created through the platform
  • Product support available from both TikTok and the partner platform
  • Security and updates will be administered by the platform


Attached here is a guide written up by a colleague that will help in your decision-making as well.


I am here as your technical resource as you move forward with TikTok measurement! Please let me know if further questions come up, and have a great weekend.


Heidi
